headlines.description: — Nikola Vucevic had 29 points and 14 rebounds, and the Chicago Bulls breezed past the Charlotte Hornets 120-99 on Thursday night with Zach LaVine back on the floor.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bulls complete sweep of Hornets in LaVine's return, 120-99

headlines.description: — Bradley Beal had 14 of his 28 points in the fourth quarter and overtime Thursday night, and Russell Westbrook had his 34th triple-double of the season in the Washington Wizards' 131-129 win over Toronto that all but eliminated the Raptors from the...
headlines.shortLinkText: Wizards beat Raptors in OT, Toronto playoff bid nearly over

headlines.description: — Wayne Ellington and Cory Joseph scored 18 points apiece to help the Detroit Pistons snap a four-game losing streak with a 111-97 victory over the Memphis Grizzlies on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pistons snap skid with 111-97 win over Grizzlies

headlines.description: — Caris LeVert scored 31 points, including nine in the final 2:17, and the Indiana Pacers awoke from a recent funk with a 133-126 victory over the Atlanta Hawks on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: LeVert's late burst helps Pacers beat Hawks 133-126

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry had 34 points and seven assists and the Golden State Warriors raced past the Oklahoma City Thunder 118-97 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Stephen Curry scores 34 points, leads Warriors past Thunder

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at LA Clippers

headlines.description: — Paul George led seven players in double figures with 24 points and the Los Angeles Clippers routed a Lakers team minus LeBron James 118-94 on Thursday night, moving into the No. 3 spot in the Western Conference playoff race.
headlines.shortLinkText: Clippers rout Lakers 118-94, move into No. 3 spot in West
